finalGrades.commentValue: Nico is a very intelligent, hard working student. He is one of the most creative students in his class. Nico is a leader in our Socratic Seminars. He is a fine writer; however, he needs to work on sentence fluency.

Nicolas has demonstrated a good understanding of the course content. His work has demonstrated a clear improvement in his understanding of the mathematics thus far studied. His work is more organized and better communicates his ideas. It is recommended that they complete one full exam (available on Haiku) using any notes and or textbooks. This is meant to expose them to the length, depth and content of the exam without the added pressure of having mastered all the concepts.

Nico continues to improve as a student. He is performing better than ever on tests. He makes it to first period on time almost all the time now. And his maturity in quietly allowing others the time to digest and understand material that he is expert in during the most recent unit on electronics was nice to see. I'm impressed, both with Nico's intelligence and with his growing maturity.

Nico has made very good progress over the course of the semester. In both the essay and the presentation he utilized the outlining and drafting process to provide generally complete work. This allowed him to get quality feedback and he was very attentive to make changes. He listened carefully to feedback and incorporated many good changes into his final assessments. He is a considerate student in class. I wish you the best of luck in your last semester.

Nico has shown exemplary progress this semester in terms of his writing. I am very pleased at the improvement he has made. Initially he was visibly frustrated with me and his grades, but has since shown a willingness to learn and improve that has been notable. The quality of his writing on the last test was impressive. I hope Nico will continue to listen to suggestions and improve further next semester.

Nicco has made excellent progress in all the language skills in Spanish. He participates actively in class and has given very good presentations. He did very well in his oral exam and in his Written task. I encourage him to continue trying his best next semester.

Nico is without a doubt a well versed programmer and skilled at developing sophisticated algorithms. However, he has had difficulty with the theoretical parts of this course. He has no problem with understanding the concepts and topics but struggles with articulating this properly on assessments. Nico realizes this and has worked hard especially during these past couple of months to better learn how to appropriately answer questions on assignments and assessments. I believe that at this current pace, he will have no problem in achieving his goal.
